=== Verb ===
'''[[byť#Slovak|byť]]''' (second person singular: '''si''')
# (you) [[are]], (thou) [[art]]
=== Reflexive Pronoun ===
'''si'''

Bound with many Slovak verbs, similar to the German [[sich]] or Italian [[si#Italian|si]], however, only used as a [[dative]], ''to oneself'' or ''for myself'': '''kúpil som ''si'' auto''', ''I bought "me" a car''. There is no way to just say ''I bought a car'' in Slovak without the '''si'''.

Not to be confused with '''[[sa]]''' which is another reflexive pronoun, but used as an [[accusative]].
